text: Razack may refer to: *Abdool Razack Mohamed Kt, MP (1906–1978), Indian born former key Mauritian Minister in the pre and post-independence cabinet of Mauritius *Abdou Razack Traoré (born 1988), Ivorian-born Burkinabe footballer *Abraham Razack, SBS, JP (born 1945), the member of the Legislative Council of Hong Kong (LegCo) *K. M. Abdul Razack, Indian politician and former Member of the Legislative Assembly of Tamil Nadu *Sherene Razack, a Canadian postcolonial, anti-racist feminist scholar and activist of Indian descent ==See also== *Fatel Razack, the first ship to bring indentured labourers from India to Trinidad
title: Razack
